- I don't know.

259
00:17:54,396 --> 00:17:56,729
I only came
to bring him something important.

260
00:17:56,812 --> 00:17:59,521
That's absolutely forbidden
and Kylian knows it.

261
00:17:59,604 --> 00:18:01,646
- I'll report it.
- He came without telling me.

262
00:18:01,729 --> 00:18:03,396
I was about to go to bed.

263
00:18:03,479 --> 00:18:05,854
All right, then. Leave.

264
00:18:16,229 --> 00:18:19,229
[introspective music playing]

265
00:18:24,562 --> 00:18:25,979
[Kingsley exhales]

266
00:18:26,062 --> 00:18:29,021
[Kingsley softly] No way, brother.
There's no way.

267
00:18:29,687 --> 00:18:31,604
- [Kingsley sucks teeth]
- [wood thuds]

268
00:18:31,687 --> 00:18:33,937
I'm gonna smash this phone, I swear.

269
00:18:34,021 --> 00:18:35,229
[exhales]

270
00:18:35,937 --> 00:18:37,437
[Léo] What are you doing?

271
00:18:40,937 --> 00:18:42,104
You see this?

272
00:18:42,771 --> 00:18:44,062
It's Kylian's.

273
00:18:44,729 --> 00:18:47,562
That psycho had two phones.
Meanwhile, we're starving from hunger.

274
00:18:47,646 --> 00:18:49,104
Can you believe this?

275
00:18:49,729 --> 00:18:50,729
No.

276
00:18:51,312 --> 00:18:53,104
What might the code be? You have any idea?

277
00:18:59,021 --> 00:19:00,562
I'm sure that SherKhan gave him this.

278
00:19:01,229 --> 00:19:02,437
SherKhan?

279
00:19:03,521 --> 00:19:06,229
I'm sure that he's running errands
for SherKhan…

280
00:19:06,312 --> 00:19:09,979
or maybe SherKhan has him by the balls.

281
00:19:10,062 --> 00:19:11,771
I don't know, man. [sucks teeth]

282
00:19:11,854 --> 00:19:12,979
[phone clatters]

283
00:19:13,479 --> 00:19:14,479
[sighs]

284
00:19:14,562 --> 00:19:17,479
Should've never let him
have shady pals like Fatso.

285
00:19:17,562 --> 00:19:20,271
Does Fatso also work for SherKhan?

286
00:19:21,521 --> 00:19:22,604
I'm not sure.

287
00:19:28,812 --> 00:19:29,812
I have an idea.

288
00:19:29,896 --> 00:19:32,271
["Ga letaw!" by DLF playing]

289
00:19:40,104 --> 00:19:42,271
[SherKhan] Everyone's gonna say
I'm the villain here.

290
00:19:42,354 --> 00:19:44,854
Well, maybe you should
settle your issue with that man.

291
00:19:44,937 --> 00:19:47,562
Trust, I'm gonna settle it.
I'm gonna shoot these fools for real.

292
00:19:47,646 --> 00:19:50,104
Khan, there's a kid
who wants to talk to you.

293
00:19:50,187 --> 00:19:52,396
- Who?
- He doesn't want to tell us his name.

294
00:19:52,479 --> 00:19:54,312
- Is he clean?
- Yeah.

295
00:19:54,396 --> 00:19:56,396
[rap song continues playing]

296
00:20:07,562 --> 00:20:09,104
Lafleur.

297
00:20:09,937 --> 00:20:12,812
Your brother steals from me
and you show up here all calm?

298
00:20:12,896 --> 00:20:15,521
- What do you want?
- I want to work for you too, Khan.

299
00:20:16,104 --> 00:20:17,104
"You too"?

300
00:20:17,687 --> 00:20:19,687
- Yes.
- Do you know anyone working for me?

301
00:20:20,771 --> 00:20:23,104
As you can see, I'm not hiring right now.

302
00:20:24,187 --> 00:20:26,271
I don't mean here.

303
00:20:26,354 --> 00:20:27,354
Where?

304
00:20:28,187 --> 00:20:29,187
Well, you know.

305
00:20:29,271 --> 00:20:33,062
It's my only business. I'll keep you
in mind if I open another bar.

306
00:20:34,479 --> 00:20:35,896
I mean on the street, you know?

307
00:20:35,979 --> 00:20:39,479
Street, huh? You want
to sweep my yard and clean my house?

308
00:20:39,562 --> 00:20:40,771
You want to be my bitch?

309
00:20:41,271 --> 00:20:44,604
[sucks teeth] I don't employ Lafleurs.
Just ask Milord.

310
00:20:45,104 --> 00:20:46,146
Milord?

311
00:20:48,771 --> 00:20:51,437
Your brother and Milord are like this,
and with Fatso,

312
00:20:51,521 --> 00:20:53,062
and all the guys from Dillon.

313
00:20:53,146 --> 00:20:56,354
They think they saved his ass?
From where I stand, they saved nobody.

314
00:20:56,937 --> 00:20:58,437
You want to work for me?

315
00:20:59,771 --> 00:21:02,729
Go to Dillon,
put a bullet in your brother,

316
00:21:02,812 --> 00:21:04,896
and I swear you'll be my number-one guy.

317
00:21:05,562 --> 00:21:06,854
[scoffs]

318
00:21:07,812 --> 00:21:08,812
Scram, kid.

319
00:21:12,146 --> 00:21:14,229
Thanks for the headache, bro. Damn kids.

320
00:21:14,312 --> 00:21:15,312
Pleasure's all mine.

321
00:21:18,937 --> 00:21:19,937
Ah, press here.

322
00:21:20,729 --> 00:21:22,187
- Here?
- Yeah.

323
00:21:22,812 --> 00:21:24,146
Now press harder.

324
00:21:24,937 --> 00:21:26,896
[sighs and sucks teeth]

325
00:21:26,979 --> 00:21:29,146
He can't just disrespect me like that.

326
00:21:29,896 --> 00:21:32,854
- Did you take any medicine?
- No, I haven't yet.

327
00:21:33,521 --> 00:21:34,896
[knock on door]

328
00:21:35,604 --> 00:21:37,521
Nolan, it's almost your turn.

329
00:21:38,187 --> 00:21:39,687
Are we coming home?

330
00:21:39,771 --> 00:21:42,812
It's driving me crazy, brother.
He doesn't even visit y'all.

331
00:21:42,896 --> 00:21:45,604
But the worst part?
He goes and steals all of my money.

332
00:21:45,687 --> 00:21:46,979
It's bullshit.

333
00:21:48,354 --> 00:21:49,562
[Mathis] Are you okay?

334
00:21:49,646 --> 00:21:51,271
No, I'll take an aspirin.

335
00:21:51,354 --> 00:21:54,021
[grunts] This is really busting my head.

336
00:21:57,521 --> 00:21:59,521
[shower running]

337
00:22:02,979 --> 00:22:05,146
Thaïs, are there any painkillers in there?

338
00:22:05,229 --> 00:22:06,812
[Willy] Uh, yeah. Hold on.

339
00:22:06,896 --> 00:22:10,229
- [dark music playing]
- Thaïs, are you in there too?

340
00:22:10,312 --> 00:22:12,979
- [Thaïs] Yes, I'm almost finished.
- [lock clicks]

341
00:22:17,771 --> 00:22:20,521
- [shower continues running]
- [dark music continues]

342
00:22:20,604 --> 00:22:22,354
What are you doing here, man?

343
00:22:22,854 --> 00:22:26,062
Just freshening up for the day.
We only have one bathroom.

344
00:22:26,146 --> 00:22:27,562
Could you put on some pants?

345
00:22:28,229 --> 00:22:30,146
What's happening here?

346
00:22:30,229 --> 00:22:32,646
What the hell is this about? Get out!

347
00:22:33,771 --> 00:22:36,021
Nolan, Mathis, over here.

348
00:22:38,021 --> 00:22:40,312
Does Uncle Willy
get naked often in front of you?

349
00:22:42,104 --> 00:22:44,562
Does he enter the room when you shower?

350
00:22:45,396 --> 00:22:47,062
- No.
- No.

351
00:22:47,562 --> 00:22:49,146
He does with Thaïs.

352
00:22:49,937 --> 00:22:51,437
Get your stuff, we're leaving.

353
00:22:51,521 --> 00:22:52,687
- King?
- Shut up!

354
00:22:52,771 --> 00:22:55,562
- You need to calm down, King.
- Shut the fuck up.

355
00:22:56,062 --> 00:22:58,062
[dark music continues]

356
00:23:00,729 --> 00:23:02,979
- Let's go. Faster, faster.
- What's going on here?

357
00:23:03,062 --> 00:23:05,687
- Faster! I'm taking them home now.
- Have you lost your mind?

358
00:23:05,771 --> 00:23:08,896
Let's go. Come on.
[sighs] Your husband is a fucking pervert!

359
00:23:08,979 --> 00:23:11,062
That's bull.
You only see the bad, don't you?

360
00:23:11,146 --> 00:23:13,187
You also gonna claim
she asked him to be her pimp?

361
00:23:13,271 --> 00:23:15,646
That right? [sucks teeth]
We leaving. Come on. Move.

362
00:23:15,729 --> 00:23:18,646
No! You have no right to take them.

363
00:23:18,729 --> 00:23:21,021
Willy! Call the police!

364
00:23:21,104 --> 00:23:23,271
Be my guest, please!

365
00:23:23,354 --> 00:23:28,229
If you call the police, that damn judge,
the social worker, whatever…

366
00:23:28,312 --> 00:23:33,187
I don't give a fuck. I'll come back here
and burn down you and your damn house.

367
00:23:33,271 --> 00:23:34,729
Understand?

368
00:23:36,521 --> 00:23:39,521
["SO COMAN" by Kalash playing]

369
00:23:47,146 --> 00:23:52,271
Mathis has a CT scan scheduled for Monday!
You're gonna have to pay it upfront.

370
00:23:52,354 --> 00:23:54,062
Keep walking, keep walking.

371
00:23:55,521 --> 00:23:57,687
What's the CT scan for? You okay?

372
00:23:57,771 --> 00:24:00,937
Because I get dizzy sometimes,
usually at night.

373
00:24:01,021 --> 00:24:02,187
Dizzy?

374
00:24:02,271 --> 00:24:03,271
Yeah.

375
00:24:07,937 --> 00:24:10,937
- [Mathis] What's a scan?
- ["SO COMAN" continues playing]

376
00:24:42,687 --> 00:24:45,687
- [song fading]
- [waves lapping gently]

377
00:25:06,771 --> 00:25:07,979
Here.

378
00:25:08,479 --> 00:25:10,479
New phone? Thank you.

379
00:25:20,396 --> 00:25:22,021
- [Fatso] Call Marco, Kylian.
- No.

380
00:25:22,104 --> 00:25:24,354
What don't you understand?
We're not going anywhere.

381
00:25:24,437 --> 00:25:25,937
And if they never appear?

382
00:25:27,312 --> 00:25:28,687
Why wouldn't they appear?

383
00:25:28,771 --> 00:25:30,854
To keep the money
of a punk they don't care about.

384
00:25:32,437 --> 00:25:34,229
- Am I the punk?
- What did you say?

385
00:25:34,937 --> 00:25:37,854
- Isn't the punk helping you eat?
- We work, you pay.

386
00:25:37,937 --> 00:25:39,312
Shut up, Ludo.

387
00:25:40,354 --> 00:25:42,896
The dope we're about to get,
did you work for that?

388
00:25:43,812 --> 00:25:46,854
The shipping containers.
Was it you that found them?

389
00:25:47,729 --> 00:25:49,937
Do you know how much money you'll make?

390
00:25:50,021 --> 00:25:52,562
Nothing. He won't get a damn thing.

391
00:25:52,646 --> 00:25:55,062
Calm down.
No need to get mad like this, okay?

392
00:25:55,146 --> 00:25:56,687
I'm just saying, man.

393
00:25:58,104 --> 00:25:59,521
[emphatically] I'm with you.

394
00:26:00,479 --> 00:26:02,479
[motorboat approaching in distance]

395
00:26:03,396 --> 00:26:04,646
[Kylian] Shh!

396
00:26:12,187 --> 00:26:14,187
[motorboat approaching]

397
00:27:27,062 --> 00:27:28,979
Take this back. We'll sell it locally.

398
00:27:29,062 --> 00:27:31,812
- We need to make money right away.
- Okay.

399
00:27:32,646 --> 00:27:33,729
And…

400
00:27:35,937 --> 00:27:41,146
Don't pay attention to my brother.
He can be idiot, but he's pretty straight.

401
00:27:41,229 --> 00:27:43,229
["AK47" by Mercenaire & Kalash playing]

402
00:28:03,062 --> 00:28:04,812
Don't call me "little punk."

403
00:28:08,146 --> 00:28:11,271
["AK47" continues playing]

404
00:28:25,187 --> 00:28:28,771
JC - I warned you.
It's over. Forget about me.

405
00:28:41,979 --> 00:28:44,979
["AK47" continues playing]

406
00:29:12,271 --> 00:29:14,271
[song fading]

407
00:29:14,354 --> 00:29:16,896
- [dog barking]
- [Ludo] Shut it!

408
00:29:18,979 --> 00:29:20,396
[growls softly]

409
00:29:22,521 --> 00:29:23,646
Damn dog.

410
00:30:06,729 --> 00:30:08,146
[dog barking]

411
00:30:09,646 --> 00:30:10,937
[dog growls softly]

412
00:30:12,271 --> 00:30:14,521
- [barking continues]
- [man] Is anyone here?

413
00:30:18,896 --> 00:30:20,771
- [barking continues]
- Shut up!

414
00:30:20,854 --> 00:30:22,854
Excuse me, I think we may be lost.

415
00:30:22,937 --> 00:30:25,271
- Where'd you come from?
- The woods back here.

416
00:30:26,146 --> 00:30:29,521
Cross the field over there.
Walk down the path.

417
00:30:29,604 --> 00:30:31,062
It's marked.

418
00:30:31,729 --> 00:30:34,812
- I'm sorry, but do you have any water?
- No, none here.

419
00:30:35,437 --> 00:30:36,562
Is there a problem?

420
00:30:36,646 --> 00:30:37,771
[Ludo] No problem.

421
00:30:42,354 --> 00:30:44,604
We don't mean to disturb. We'll go.

422
00:30:45,437 --> 00:30:46,729
[Kylian] Your passports.

423
00:30:50,146 --> 00:30:52,604
- [gun cocks]
- Your passports, now.

424
00:30:54,729 --> 00:30:57,729
[tense music playing]

425
00:31:11,771 --> 00:31:12,896
[Fatso] Marseille.

426
00:31:13,396 --> 00:31:15,437
Tons of people work for me there.

427
00:31:17,312 --> 00:31:19,812
Sir, please. We just want to go home.

428
00:31:45,521 --> 00:31:46,854
Fuck off.

429
00:31:48,646 --> 00:31:50,187
[dog barks]

430
00:31:50,729 --> 00:31:52,646
When are we moving this to the dock?

431
00:31:55,437 --> 00:31:56,437
[sighs]

432
00:31:57,229 --> 00:31:58,479
In three days.

433
00:31:58,979 --> 00:32:02,187
[Marvin] That's not the subject
of this conversation. It's not.

434
00:32:02,271 --> 00:32:03,396
Kylian.

435
00:32:03,479 --> 00:32:04,479
Where were you?

436
00:32:04,562 --> 00:32:06,896
- I was in the forest with Lily.
- [Marvin scoffs]

437
00:32:06,979 --> 00:32:08,062
Can I take a quick shower?

438
00:32:08,146 --> 00:32:10,146
I don't have time to wait on his highness.

439
00:32:12,979 --> 00:32:13,979
Are they at school?

440
00:32:15,021 --> 00:32:18,021
Given what happened, we don't think
we should send them back to Régine's.

441
00:32:18,104 --> 00:32:19,187
- Do you agree?
- Well, yeah.

442
00:32:19,271 --> 00:32:21,104
[Kingsley] Anyway,
we don't want his opinion.

443
00:32:22,062 --> 00:32:24,396
We've gotta handle this.
It's gonna be tough.

444
00:32:24,479 --> 00:32:26,104
Money problems first.

445
00:32:26,771 --> 00:32:30,271
That scan for Mathis isn't covered.
Gonna be expensive as hell.

446
00:32:30,354 --> 00:32:31,896
You'll pay up, yeah?

447
00:32:31,979 --> 00:32:34,271
Hmm? You've got a plan, I assume.

448
00:32:34,354 --> 00:32:36,604
Or else you wouldn't have fucked up mine.

449
00:32:37,104 --> 00:32:40,396
We had 400,000 euros to live on like men.

450
00:32:40,479 --> 00:32:42,271
What do you propose then, Kylian?

451
00:32:43,646 --> 00:32:45,937
You had it
in your little princess hands, huh?

452
00:32:46,021 --> 00:32:47,479
Only to give it to that asshole?

453
00:32:47,562 --> 00:32:49,604
So you're saying
it's better for you to be killed?

454
00:32:49,687 --> 00:32:50,771
[Kingsley] Yes!

455
00:32:50,854 --> 00:32:53,229
Did you really have to do it like that?
Behind our backs.

456
00:32:56,979 --> 00:32:59,687
What are you looking at?
You know I don't agree with them, right?

457
00:32:59,771 --> 00:33:00,937
Okay, okay, okay!

458
00:33:01,021 --> 00:33:02,187
Just stop!

459
00:33:02,271 --> 00:33:04,854
Kylian just wanted to help, so stop.

460
00:33:05,354 --> 00:33:07,479
But we all have to pitch in
to make ends meet.

461
00:33:07,979 --> 00:33:10,604
Kylian, go pick up the kids from school.
We can begin with that.

462
00:33:10,687 --> 00:33:13,062
Don't forget to tell them
there won't be any school trips.

463
00:33:13,146 --> 00:33:15,812
There won't be any activities,
No costumes, no games, no parties.

464
00:33:15,896 --> 00:33:17,062
No Pokémon.

465
00:33:17,146 --> 00:33:20,979
- Because it's either that or no food.
- [Marvin] You have to help us, brother.

466
00:33:21,062 --> 00:33:22,271
I never said I wouldn't.

467
00:33:22,854 --> 00:33:24,437
Okay, move your ass, then!

468
00:33:25,021 --> 00:33:27,854
- [school bell ringing]
- [kid] Okay, see you later.

469
00:33:27,937 --> 00:33:29,687
[kids chattering indistinctly]

470
00:33:33,437 --> 00:33:35,521
[kid] I've never seen his brother before!

471
00:33:35,604 --> 00:33:36,687
[laughs]

472
00:33:37,979 --> 00:33:39,354
Is that you?

473
00:33:39,437 --> 00:33:40,646
Yeah.

474
00:33:40,729 --> 00:33:42,604
But you don't pick us up usually.

475
00:33:43,271 --> 00:33:46,479
I know, but today I'm here.
Not disappointed, are you?

476
00:33:46,562 --> 00:33:48,896
- [Thaïs] No, it's really great.
- [Nolan] No, it's great.

477
00:33:48,979 --> 00:33:50,229
[Léo] Yeah!

478
00:33:50,771 --> 00:33:53,187
- [Kylian] How you doin'?
- I'm fine.

479
00:33:53,271 --> 00:33:56,312
- [Nolan] Are we going home?
- Yeah, someone's picking us up.

480
00:34:00,062 --> 00:34:02,437
Well, I won't say anything to the judge.

481
00:34:02,521 --> 00:34:05,187
I'll just take back the children.
You've already suffered.

482
00:34:05,271 --> 00:34:06,479
No.

483
00:34:06,562 --> 00:34:08,396
No, I have to bring them back.
Sorry, Auntie.

484
00:34:08,479 --> 00:34:11,021
Kylian, be reasonable, not like Kingsley.

485
00:34:11,604 --> 00:34:13,979
- Come here, children. The car is--
- [Nolan] Mmm!

486
00:34:14,729 --> 00:34:15,896
- Let go.
- Leave, Régine.

487
00:34:17,021 --> 00:34:19,229
They won't be going back with you.
Drop it.

488
00:34:19,937 --> 00:34:21,146
Yeah? Or else what?

489
00:34:21,729 --> 00:34:23,521
You don't want to know, believe me.

490
00:34:24,021 --> 00:34:25,187
[Régine straining]

491
00:34:29,271 --> 00:34:32,562
Poor Marilyn.
You truly are a bunch of thugs.

492
00:34:32,646 --> 00:34:35,979
["Love" by X-Man & Matieu White playing]

493
00:34:37,437 --> 00:34:38,896
[Mathis] So cool!

494
00:34:40,979 --> 00:34:42,396
You two are going with them.

495
00:34:42,479 --> 00:34:43,646
[Fatso] Hop on, Mathis.

496
00:34:44,271 --> 00:34:45,854
[Kylian] Give me the helmet?

497
00:34:46,771 --> 00:34:49,021
[Mathis] So awesome.

498
00:34:54,271 --> 00:34:56,187
- You okay?
- Yeah.

499
00:34:57,479 --> 00:34:58,854
You feeling dizzy?

500
00:35:01,479 --> 00:35:03,479
- You sure you'll be all right?
- Mmm.

501
00:35:03,562 --> 00:35:05,979
Tell me if you don't feel well. Let's go.

502
00:35:06,062 --> 00:35:09,062
["Love" continues playing]

503
00:35:16,812 --> 00:35:19,104
[indistinct chatter]

504
00:35:19,187 --> 00:35:23,229
I have also some avocados.
They're four for the price of two.

505
00:35:23,312 --> 00:35:25,062
And also some fresh tomatoes.

506
00:35:25,146 --> 00:35:27,146
Add them to some fish,
they go with everything.

507
00:35:27,229 --> 00:35:28,979
- Did you see these?
